## OpenAPI Version Fix (scriptbots-app/src/servers.rs)

### Problem

`utoipa`'s derive macro required compile-time constant for version, but `env!("CARGO_PKG_VERSION")` doesn't satisfy that in the `#[utoipa::openapi(...)]` attribute context, causing compilation errors in some configurations.

### Solution

```rust
#[derive(OpenApi)]
#[openapi(
    // ...
    info(title = "ScriptBots Control API", version = "0.0.0"),  // Placeholder
)]
struct ApiDoc;

impl ApiDoc {
    fn spec() -> utoipa::openapi::OpenApi {
        let mut doc = ApiDoc::openapi();
        doc.info.version = Some(env!("CARGO_PKG_VERSION").to_string());
        doc
    }
}

// Usage
let openapi = ApiDoc::spec();  // Version is now dynamic
```

Sets a placeholder version in the derive macro, then overwrites it at runtime with the actual package version.

